<subSubSection id="C309F5BFD86B965F7DAEF9E2FE9EF9D6" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BACA634D86B965F7DAEF9E2FE9EF9D6" blockId="31.[192,1440,1571,1627]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9677A26D86B965F7DAEF9E2FED6F9B6" bold="true" box="[192,343,1571,1595]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is descriptive for the aviform apex of the caudodorsal process of the pygofer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C309F5BFD86B965F7DAEF942FC57F976" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BACA634D86B965F7DAEF942FC57F976" blockId="31.[192,1440,1667,1787]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9677A26D86B965F7DAEF942FEC5F916" bold="true" box="[192,324,1667,1691]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
From 
<taxonomicName id="4C13DDB7D86B965F7CFAF945FD51F911" authority="Li and Wang" authorityName="Li and Wang" box="[404,720,1667,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hiatusorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heidainus">
<emphasis id="B9677A26D86B965F7CFAF945FDB3F916" box="[404,562,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">H. heidainus</emphasis>
Li and Wang
</taxonomicName>
to which it is similar in the apex of the pygofer caudodorsal process, 
<taxonomicName id="4C13DDB7D86B965F7C47F965FE4BF936" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2015" box="[297,458,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hiatusorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aviformus">
<emphasis id="B9677A26D86B965F7C47F965FE4BF936" box="[297,458,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">H. aviformus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by the broad subgenital plate which is not membranous on the outer lateral margin, not toothed on the margin of the incurvated aedeagus and broader anterior arms of the connective. The crown is much shorter than in 
<emphasis id="B9677A26D86B965F7E5EF925FC57F976" box="[816,982,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName id="4C13DDB7D86B965F7E5EF925FC53F976" box="[816,978,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hiatusorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heidainus">H. heidainus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
